{
  "texts": [
    "OpenAI's ChatGPT, 2 potentially exacerbating threats around disinformation and confidential data exposure [62] underscores the urgency of instituting recurring external oversight before unforeseen harms emerge at population scale.Risk Assessments The required recurring DSA risk assessments analyzing threats to electoral processes and vulnerable groups enabled by VLOP systems including proprietary algorithms (Art.",
    "34,35) highlight the necessity of mandating that AI developers comprehensively document potential dangers from creating addictive, biased or manipulative systems.",
    "As generative models like text and media synthesizers scale exponentially in sophistication, developers should increasingly bear the onus of demonstrating diligent inquiries evaluating capacities for harm.",
    "Indeed, relying purely on voluntary self-assessment of risks, in the context of the unprecedented acceleration in generative AI capabilities presaging looming threats from fake accounts, spam, phishing campaigns, disinformation floods, would prove inadequate.",
    "In this vein, the AI Act (especially Recitals 60v, 70d) [37] complements the DSA's transparency obligations on Platforms to mitigate risks from disseminating synthetically generated content, as both texts call out the specific need to adequately audit algorithms."
  ]
}